Hi,

I am migrating Blazor WASM app to Blazor MAUI and ran into an JS interop issue when calling C# method from JS:

_Uncaught Error: The current dispatcher does not support synchronous calls from JS to .NET. Use invokeMethodAsync instead.
    at v (blazor.webview.js:1:1674)
    at C.invokeMethod (blazor.webview.js:1:3812)
    at HTMLDivElement.component.onTransitionend (BlzMainLayoutSideBar.razor.js:21:52)_

```javascript
     // handle sidebar transition end event
        component.onTransitionend = function () {
            const isCollapsed = componentDotNetRef.invokeMethod("OnTransitionEnd");
            if (isCollapsed === true) {
                lib.enableBodyScrolling();
            }
        }
```

```csharp
     [JSInvokable]
        public bool OnTransitionEnd()
        {
		// ...
		return isFinished;
	}
```

Changing the JS call to C# to async seemed to fix the problem:
```javascript
       component.onTransitionend = async function () {
            const isCollapsed = await componentDotNetRef.invokeMethodAsync("OnTransitionEnd");
            if (isCollapsed === true) {
                lib.enableBodyScrolling();
            }
        }
```

Is this all that needs to be done? Or should I also change the C# method to return ``Task`` even though there are no asynchronous calls inside ``OnTransitionEnd``.

```csharp
   [JSInvokable]
        public Task<bool> OnTransitionEnd()
        {
		// ...
		return Task.FromResult(isFinished);
	}
```

I will need to modify quite a bit of existing code to make all my components compatible with Blazor MAUI so I'd like to ensure that I'm making the right change.

Thank you!



